	   <tr><td colspan=2>I would reccomend trying to max out the skills at each level.&nbsp;&nbsp;  I made the mistake of only using only 1hs.  I got a runed falchion and never looked back.  At higher levels, most choose to have a wisdom item in each hand, and melee becomes trivial, however, with the release of the kunark stuff, I regret that i don't have max in all 3.  <br><br>Wisdom is important, and saying that someone should put away their 9 Wis CGS and their 9 WIS Paw in favor of a lower wisdom (i think 5-8) Luminecent staff may sound crazy, but your wisdom pool should be high enough that you can take the hit and still go on trucking as a valid caster.<br><br>Although, as said above, much after the 30ith level, druid are to cast and med, it is nice to be able to melee every now and then.   If you got your heart set on a tunarian schmitar, max out your 1hs.  If you want a luminecent staff, go for 2hb.  If you want a springwood club or a jorneyman's walkingstick, go for 1hb.    However, I'd think that people would want all of 'em, so max 'em all out.  (or at least try).<br><br><br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
