	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Default<span id=notbold>[2.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>by level 40, probably 90% of all druids run around without a weapon - they have a CGS or ToV in one hand and the Paw of Opalla in the other. I think the only 1hs with any wisdom is the tunarian scimmy (+6 wis) - and you have to kill a God to get it. A charred guardian shield gives you 9 wisdom and 10 ac, and you can get one for about 500pp on my server. You'll have alot of trouble finding a 2hb for that much that gives you anywhere near that Wis. As for 1hb, there are tons of them with wisdom out there, knobbed warclub (+ 3), springwood club (+5), iskar berserker club (+4), enchanted&nbsp;&nbsp;FS morning star (+5), shilleghleh (+9 ??) - druids were meant to use 1hb. Problem is, that our cap for our casting skills is 5 points per level, our cap for weapons skills is 4 points per level, not to mention that your AC is always going to suck because you can't wear plate or chain (I am aware of the exceptions - but realistically feasable for most?) - bottom line, druids are casters(you can't kick, you can't bash, you can't dual weild, you can't double attack, you can't parry, you're capped on dodge, you can't riposte and you can't wear plate so your AC sucks - you're a caster, get over it). And just because you can beat up low blues now, you won't be able to later - believe it (remember the first time you tried to melee a blue griffawn?)I don't bother with 1hs or 2hb cause I don't want to get caught with less wisdom than I should have. Wisdom is primary because you're a caster, not a tank. Verant designed your weapons skills to suck and your casting skills to be great, and your AC to be low so take a hint.<br>I will say this though, just because your weapon doesn't deal out much damage that doesn't make it useless. The most important thing you'll be doing with your weapon when you solo is interrupting spells. Theres nothing like beating the hell out of a cleric type mob and then have him cast greater healing on himself - that turns an easy fight into a close one. Its a forunate thing to be able to interrupt that spell. So whatever you do, get a nice quick weapon - I'd say delay 24 or lower if you can, preferably one with some Wis (like an iskar berserker club is a great one). If you've ever camped the mammoth cloak, you know how important this is. Interrupting spells is the only reason you're really going to have to swing a weapon. And that makes dexterity and weapon skills important.<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
